 pull files from repositrory using git gui is:
   open the tab Tools and choose Add option.
   enter a name, and as command enter git pull <remote> <branch>
   
   add files in git repository using git bash is:
     1) git init
	 2) git add . or git add ['filename'] or git add <folder>/*,or even git add *
	 3) git commit -m "My first File"
	 4) git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git
	 5) git pull origin master
	 6) git push origin master
	 
	 
	 remove directories in git repositrory using git bash is:
	 
		In the command-line, navigate to your local repository.
		Ensure you are in the  branch from which you want to delete folders:
		1)git checkout master
		2)git rm -r folder-name(this will delete  the folder from  both local and remote git repository),
		   git rm -r --cached folder-name(this will delete the folder only from remote git repository).
		3)git commit -m "Remove duplicated directory"
		4)git push origin master
	        **in place of master you can write the required branch name***